== Mention of Quartodeciman controversy ==

Mention of the Quartodeciman controversy in this article arose out of an edit by Leadwind on [http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=East–West_Schism&diff=199837152&oldid=199580504 21 March 2008] stating: "Prior to the official start of the schism, Eastern and Western Christians had a history of difference and disagreement ''dating back to the second century''."  When the phrase I have italicized was questioned (by me) on the grounds of lack of evidence of trouble between Rome and the East (as a whole) that far back, Orthotheo responded with the example of the Quartodeciman controversy.  If Leadwind's claim is not maintained, the mention of the controversy will go too.  [[User:Esoglou|Esoglou]] ([[User talk:Esoglou|talk]]) 06:55, 20 October 2012 (UTC)

